## Why I chose to major in Management Information Systems

I chose to major in Management Information Systems because of its dynamic blend between the business world and technology. 
I felt that this major would help equip me with the skills necessary to become an expert of technology and become a business leader. 
Through MIS, I hope to become knowledgable of cybersecurity, project management, and data analysis. 
The versatility of MIS was appealing to me through its possiblity of working in various industries.
Overall, I felt that MIS was a major worth investing in, where I would find a promising career reshaping businesses in an increasingly digital world.
